Rohit likes to play with numbers. He started to frame a matrix called uniformity matrix where he will be using either completely odd numbers or completely even numbers but not both. Write a program to check whether he has framed the matrix in the correct order or not.

Input Format

The input consists of (n*n+1) integers. The first integer corresponds to the number of rows/columns in the matrix. The remaining integers correspond to the elements in the matrix. The elements are read in row-wise order, the first row first, then the second row, and so on.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

Print Yes if it is a uniformity matrix. Print No if it is not a uniformity matrix.

Sample Input 0

2
4 5
5 4
Sample Output 0

No


import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
       int n=sc.nextInt();
       int arr[][]=new int[n][n];
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
       {
        for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
        {
            arr[i][j]=sc.nextInt();
        }
       }
       int e=0;
       int o=0;
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
       {
        for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
        {
            if(arr[i][j]%2==0)
            {
                e++;
            }
            else
            {
                o++;
            }
        }
       }
       if(e==n*n || o==n*n)
       System.out.print("Yes");
       else System.out.print("No");
    }
}

